{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "AIDLC Phase Guard",
  "description": "Before writing files in .aidlc/ outputs or tests/, verify prerequisite phase outputs exist and decision+plan files are created.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "preToolUse",
    "toolTypes": ["write"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Check the file path being written. ONLY apply this check if the path contains '.aidlc/' OR 'tests/' OR 'mock-pages/'. If the path is in .kiro/, .claude/skills/, .memory/, or any other location — SKIP this hook silently and proceed.\n\nIf the path IS in .aidlc/ or tests/ or mock-pages/:\n\n1. Check AIDLC phase prerequisites:\n   - tests/ or mock-pages/ → qa-architecture.md AND test-cases.md must exist in .aidlc outputs\n   - qa-architecture.md → test-cases.md must exist\n   - test-cases.md → logical-design.md must exist\n   - logical-design.md → domain-design.md must exist\n   - domain-design.md → domain-decomposition.md must exist\n   - domain-decomposition.md → user-stories.md must exist\n\n2. Check decision+plan files exist for the current phase:\n   - Each phase output MUST have a corresponding decision file in planning/decisions/\n   - If decision file is missing → remind to create it first\n\nIf prerequisites missing → STOP and inform user. Otherwise proceed."
  }
}
